<!-- S4: SATURATION -->
<section class="hidden stagger-2" id="s4">
<div class="section-label">04 · HARMONIC GENERATION</div>
<div class="section-title">Saturation Modulation Systems</div>
<div class="section-sub">Analog saturation is not merely clipping — it is the nonlinear transfer characteristic of transformer cores, tape oxide, and triode amplifiers generating even and odd harmonics as the input exceeds the linear operating range. The result: apparent loudness, perceived warmth, natural compression.</div>
