<div class="section-label">06 · NONLINEAR BEHAVIOR</div>
<div class="section-title">Harmonic Distortion Systems</div>
<div class="section-sub">Analog warmth is an audible bias toward even-order harmonics — the 2nd, 4th, 6th partials above the fundamental. Triode vacuum tubes and Class-A transformer circuits generate predominantly even harmonics. Hard clipping generates odd harmonics. The ratio determines the character.</div>
